    "# Lab 1.3: Memory Hierarchy & Access Patterns\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🎯 Learning Objectives\n",
    "By completing this lab, you will:\n",
    "1. **Understand** GPU memory hierarchy and its performance implications\n",
    "2. **Measure** the cost of different memory access patterns\n",
    "3. **Optimize** data layouts for better cache utilization\n",
    "4. **Analyze** memory bandwidth bottlenecks in transformers\n",
    "5. **Implement** memory-aware algorithms\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🧠 Why Memory Hierarchy Matters\n",
    "The memory hierarchy is the **biggest determinant** of real-world performance:\n",
    "- Registers: 1 cycle access, ~10 TB/s bandwidth\n",
    "- Shared memory: ~20 cycles, ~3 TB/s  \n",
    "- L1/L2 cache: ~100 cycles, ~2 TB/s\n",
    "- HBM/GDDR6: ~300 cycles, 0.8-2 TB/s\n",
    "- **1000× difference** between fastest and slowest memory!\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🧪 Lab Structure\n",
    "This lab has **4 parts**, each exploring memory hierarchy:\n",
    "1. **Memory Hierarchy Basics**: Measure different memory types\n",
    "2. **Access Pattern Analysis**: How data layout affects performance\n",
    "3. **Transformer Memory Patterns**: Specific patterns in transformers\n",
    "4. **Optimization Techniques**: Memory-aware optimizations\n",
    "\n",
    "## 🔧 Setup"
   ]
  },
